articles.author: Vivian Sequera, Mircely Guanipa
articles.description: Venezuelan opposition parties and their supporters were holding protests around the country on Thursday in an eleventh-hour effort to put pressure on President Nicolas Maduro, one day before he is due to be sworn in for his third six-year term.
articles.title: As Maduro inauguration looms, Venezuela opposition hold street protests

articles.author: Rollo Ross, Jackie Luna
articles.description: Wildfires raged deep into the storied heartland of the American film industry.
articles.title: Hollywood Hills burn as LA engulfed by 'the big one'

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: As talks continued in Qatar, the Israeli military carried out strikes across the enclave, killing at least 17 people, Palestinian medics said.
articles.title: U.S., Arab mediators make some progress in Gaza peace talks, no deal yet, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanese lawmakers began voting in a presidential election on Thursday, aiming to fill a post which has been vacant since 2022, with political sources expecting army commander General Joseph Aoun to be elected.
articles.title: Lebanese lawmakers start voting on new president

articles.author: Patricia Zengerle
articles.description: The U.S. House of Representatives voted on Thursday to sanction the International Criminal Court to protest its issuing arrest warrants for Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his former defense minister over Israel's campaign in Gaza.
articles.title: US House votes to sanction International Criminal Court over Israel

articles.author: Emma Farge
articles.description: A U.N. committee found that Australia violated a human rights treaty by detaining a group of asylum seekers, including minors, on the remote Pacific island of Nauru even after they were granted refugee status, it said in a statement on Thursday.
articles.title: Australia violated refugees' rights in offshore detention centre, says UN

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau on Wednesday said U.S. President-elect Donald Trump's talk of possibly annexing Canada was a tactic designed to distract people from the impact of his proposed tariffs.
articles.title: Trudeau says Trump talk of annexing Canada is a distraction tactic

articles.author: Elida Moreno
articles.description: Hundreds of Panamanians marched on Thursday to mark the anniversary of a deadly uprising against U.S. control of the Panama Canal in 1964, with some protesters burning an effigy of President-elect Donald Trump who has threatened to retake the vital global waterway.
articles.title: As Panama remembers bloody past, a message for Trump: the canal is ours

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The brief arrest of Venezuelan opposition leader Maria Corina Machado provoked swift condemnations on Thursday from political leaders across the globe, punctuated by calls for her right to free speech and personal safety.
articles.title: Global reactions to the brief detention of Venezuela opposition leader Machado

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Four people were killed on Thursday in instances of shelling in Ukraine, one blamed on Russia's military, the other on Ukrainian forces, regional officials said.
articles.title: Four dead in shelling incidents in Ukraine, officials say
